<br>
First off, the 25k entry fee is right out. That's just too extreme for a small, friendly tournament I would think. But what should an entry fee be set at? 1k? 5k? 10k? I guess it's what the participants are willing to wager on their chances and how much they want to win. I figure (assuming we can at least get 10 teams), if we offered 20% of the pot for 3rd, 30% for 2nd, and 50% for first, that gaurantees that you at least get double your money back for placing, and a nice reward for winning overall. <br>
<br>
Secondly, I don't think 18 member teams are feasible, lol. Though allowing two alternates is a good idea, since we don't want LD disqualifying a team, and it allows an extra level of strategy, letting you shuffle around classes as need be. Would six member teams be a good idea? Hopefully that would make the fight quick and to the point. I'm open to whatever number you guys feel is best.<br>
<br>
Level limits are an excellent idea. Some of the smaller guilds might have a hard time putting together a group of 6 level 60 players. Verant uses a level limit of 1060 total for 18 players... divided into 3 that's 353 levels for a six person team. Maybe 300 would be a better figure? Or 325? It would mean for every exceptionally strong person on your team, you'll have a not so strong person there also. The main issue is, I don't want levels to determine the fight, I'd like to see them won by skill and teamwork. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Of course if you think any of my ideas are goofy, let me know what you'd like the rules to be set to and I'll see about making you happy. Before this is all over I'll type up the rules in a more readable format than my ramblings, so fear not. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, check out the ToT link and read their spell restrictions if you would, and let me know if you think they're too extreme or what. Thanks. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Almore, Ranger of the 45th<BR>
Soldier of Ministry of Steel<BR>
